						               													<description>This is a &amp;quot;Teams&amp;quot; version of the former &amp;quot;Penalty Challenge&amp;quot; game. In this version every player will be dealt a complete team of 11 players, with a similar set of shooting directions and star players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players will also be given specific goalkeeper gloves to manage during the game, so in this version the goalkeeper will have a more strategic role and in every shot the defending team will decide whether to wait to see the shot direction or to risk moving to one direction and be able to use a neutral glove and occupy more goal spaces.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The mechanism is the same as in &amp;quot;Penalty Challenge&amp;quot; the original game, the team shooting will put a shooting card pointing at the intended goal and after the defending team place their goalkeeper the shooter will be revealed. If the goalkeeper guesses the direction, they will put gloves to cover the circles inside the goal. Those circles has numbers and the shooter needs to choose one empty circle and roll the die to match with one of the number of that circle. If that happens it will be a goal, otherwise the shot will be blocked.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;First team obtaining 5 goals will be the winner of the game!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
